New Zealand ermine
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:fur from a stoat
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: A weasel has a black-tipped tail and brown fur which turns white in winter. In England it is called a stoat while it has its brown coat.
Citations
Date: 0/0/1950
Source: Introduced Mammals of NZ
Author: WODZICKI
Vol / Page: 74
Edition:
Quote: [The increase in number of stoat skins supplied to the market] is due to ... secondly, the establishment of a modern fur dressing and dyeing plant in Dunedin. In consequence a new article of the fur trade called the New Zealand Ermine has been produced, and such coats are valued at 180 pounds each.
